                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to your telegram 17th, if you find disposition on the part of Colombia
                    to ask terms more favorable to Colombia than those heretofore negotiated, you
                    may intimate orally, but not in writing, that it will be useless to send a
                    special envoy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
